    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a vertical wall of whirling, razor-sharp blades made of magical energy. The wall appears within range and lasts for the duration. You can make a straight wall up to 100 feet long, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick, or a ringed wall up to 60 feet in diameter, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick. The wall provides &amp;Reference[rule=Cover]{three-quarters cover} to creatures behind it, and its space is &amp;Reference[rule=difficultterrain]{difficult terrain}.</p><p>When a creature enters the wall's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/damage 6d10 type=slashing]] damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage.</p></div>",
